6 An Act relating to special education; requiring State
Board of Education to adopt certain parental consent
7 forms; prescribing criteria for forms; prohibiting
certain actions without parental consent; requiring
8 school district make certain reasonable efforts
before certain actions; requiring certain IEP team
9 meeting; requiring notice of meeting; authorizing
State Board of Education to adopt rules; providing
10 for codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13-114.6 of Title 70, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. The State Board of Education shall adopt a separate parental
18 consent form that school districts shall use for determining whether
19 a student who has an Individualized Education Program (IEP) will
20 participate in the Oklahoma Alternate Assessment Program (OAAP),
21 pursuant to Section 11-103.6 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
22 and be provided with instruction that will be assessed by alternate
23 achievement standards that promote access to and progress in the
24 general education curriculum.
